We closed the "Prelude" issue and the epilogue of @TheUnseasonal dedicated to Vivienne Westwood with the words: "She has often been cast out by the larger fashion world, yet has always fought to make her mark. She undoubtedly knows how to live by her own rules.
Maybe there is a bit of Westwood in all of us. What if we all went above and beyond to make the world a better place? For Westwood’s work, we have only deep appreciation and love."

I feel very lucky that I was able to spend quite a few moments with "grand dame" over the years and every single time again I left filled with admiration. I’m deeply saddened by the loss but also full of hope that many more human beings will try to make the world a better place because of her.

Here only a few of the photographs I took of Vivienne Westwood over the years. A few may follow when time passes.

"ALWAYS IN LOVE" FROM THE "NIGHT SWIM" ISSUE OF @THEUNSEASONAL

"SUCCESS TO ME IS CREATING SOMETHING THAT CAN HELP OTHERS." — PETITE MELLER

RECORDING ARTIST AND DEGREE-CERTIFIED PHILOSOPHER SYVAN MELLER, BETTER KNOWN AS PETITE MELLER, INVITED US TO JOIN HER ON THE SHOOT OF THE VIDEO FOR “AEROPLANE” — THE FIRST RELEASE AFTER HER HIT SINGLE “BABY LOVE” AND HER SUCCESSFUL 2016 DEBUT ALBUM LIL EMPIRE. ON A SHEER ENDLESS DAY THAT SOON BLURRED INTO A DREAMLIKE STREAM, WE ROAMED THROUGH COUNTLESS LANDSCAPES AND LOCATIONS IN SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA. IN OUR INTERVIEW SHE TELLS US ABOUT FINDING INSPIRATION IN MUSIC AND CULTURES FROM AROUND THE WORLD, AND HOW SHE HEALS WITH POSITIVITY.

The Eternal issue features American scriptwriter James V. Hart’s infectious passion for the never-ending that ignited the production of Bram Stoker’s Dracula, directed by Francis Ford Coppola, including never-before-seen original script pages and image material; new wave and pop-art phenomenon Blondie; illusionist, parlor magician, and creator of immersive experiences Helder Guimarães; Douglas Kirkland’s exciting journey as one of Hollywood’s most beloved celebrity photographers; award-winning artist and photographer Ger Ger; and California Deserts' otherworldly Volcano House, designed by architect Harold J. Bissner. The Eternal issue also features fashion spreads and photographs of Leonardo DiCaprio, Kate Winslet, Jack Nicholson, Dennis Hopper, Andy Warhol, Marilyn Monroe, Gary Oldman, Winona Ryder, Keanu Reeves, Tom Cruise, and more.

"SOMETIMES WE WILL BE FOOLED" IN THE NEW "ETERNAL" ISSUE OF @THEUNSEASONAL

PORTUGUESE-BORN PERFORMER AND MAGICIAN HELDER GUIMARÃES NOT ONLY WON THE WORLD CHAMPIONSHIP OF MAGIC AT THE YOUNG AGE OF 23 BUT ALSO OBTAINED THE TITLE OF PARLOUR MAGICIAN OF THE YEAR TWICE. FOLLOWING HIS CAREER FOR ALMOST A DECADE, WE SAT DOWN WITH HIM FOR A SERIES OF IN-DEPTH CONVERSATIONS IN BETWEEN HIS MANY SHOWS AND CONSULTANCIES FOR SUCH ENTERTAINMENT STUDIOS AS NBC, DISNEY, AND WARNER. EVERY TIME, WE GOT SWEPT AWAY BY HIS IMMERSIVE STORYTELLING AND HIS UNIQUE APPROACHES TO SLEIGHT-OF-HAND MAGIC, AND WE ENDED UP SEEING THE WORLD A LITTLE BIT DIFFERENTLY.

"THE VOLCANO HOUSE" IN THE "ETERNAL" ISSUE OF @THEUNSEASONAL  AMERICAN ARCHITECT HAROLD J. BISSNER WAS EQUIPPED WITH AN APPETITE FOR CHALLENGES AND EXCITEMENT WHEN ENGINEER VARD WALLACE COMMISSIONED HIM IN 1967 TO CREATE THE VOLCANO HOUSE - A HOME PERCHED ATOP AN EXTINCT CINDER CONE IN CALIFORNIA’S NEWBERRY SPRINGS. THE GALACTIC-LOOKING HIDEAWAY WITH EXPENSIVE WRAPAROUND VIEWS UNLEASHED BISSNER’S TALENT, BECOMING A UNIQUE AND EXTRAORDINARY ARCHITECTURAL ICON. BISSNER’S SON, HAROLD BISSNER III, LET US IN ON HIS FATHER’S REMARKABLE ACHIEVEMENT AND WHAT IT MEANS TO THINK OUTSIDE THE BOX.
 INTERVIEW & IMAGES: GER GER INTRODUCTION: TINA GER

Before she stormed the fashion world with her 1981 debut collection, Vivienne Westwood was a primary school teacher who sometimes sold jewelry on Portobello Road. At her Fall/Winter 1993 show, then-23-year-old Naomi Campbell fell in her 9-inch platform heels. She laughed it off and continued her way down the runway, but the image was plastered across the front pages the following day.

In a recent video with British Vogue, the supermodel admitted to Westwood that other designers have asked her to fake a fall in order to make their runway shows just as memorable — to which Campbell replied, “Absolutely not. It goes against everything that I stand for. I’m not falling purposefully.”Westwood replied, “I didn’t pay any of you very much, so you can take it for granted that I didn’t pay you to fall down.”
